		<div class="post-2301 post type-post status-publish format-standard hentry category-art category-buy-buy-buy category-copyleft category-free-culture" id="post-2301">


<div class="post-headline">		<h2>			
			<a href="http://blog.ninapaley.com/2011/11/22/gnaana-avatars-of-vishnu-calendar/" rel="bookmark" title="Permanent Link to Gnaana &#8220;Avatars of Vishnu&#8221; Calendar">Gnaana &#8220;Avatars of Vishnu&#8221; Calendar</a></h2>
		</div>

<div class="post-bodycopy clearfix"><p><a href="http://www.gnaana.com/shop.php?op=categorydetail&amp;catid=95"><img style="cursor: -moz-zoom-in;" src="http://www.gnaana.com/images/uploads/dir/hindu-cal3.jpg" alt="http://www.gnaana.com/images/uploads/dir/hindu-cal3.jpg" width="664" height="1031" /></a></p>
<p>This came out really nice! A small company called <a href="http://www.gnaana.com/shop.php?op=categorydetail&amp;catid=95">Gnaana</a> used my <a href="http://blog.ninapaley.com/2011/05/06/the-avatars-of-vishnu/">Avatars of Vishnu art</a> to make a very lovely wall calendar. The art is Free Culture; the printed calendars are <a href="http://blog.ninapaley.com/2011/07/09/culture-is-anti-rivalrous/">rivalrous goods</a> which you can buy <a href="http://www.gnaana.com/shop.php?op=categorydetail&amp;catid=95">here</a>. I just got my copies, and they are really handsome.</p>
